  "prompt": "Does a blue blazer go with khaki pants?",
  "response": "Yes, a blue blazer pairs very well with khaki pants. This is a classic, timeless combination that works for both casual and semi-formal occasions. Here\u2019s why it works:\n\n1. **Color Harmony**: Blue and khaki (or beige) are complementary neutral tones that create a balanced and polished look.\n2. **Versatility**: This combination can be dressed up with a dress shirt and tie or dressed down with a polo or casual button-up shirt.\n3. **Seasonal Flexibility**: It works year-round, making it a versatile choice for various settings and climates.\n\n**Styling Tips**:\n- For a **semi-formal look**, pair the blazer with a white or light-colored dress shirt, a tie, and leather loafers or oxfords.\n- For a **casual look**, wear it with a polo shirt, a crewneck sweater, or even a casual button-up shirt, and pair with loafers or clean sneakers.\n\nAccessories like a belt and watch can elevate the outfit further. This combination is a staple in preppy and business casual wardrobes.",
